

<worksheet xml:id="A27_More-definite-integrals">
  <title>Math 150  Activity 27: More definite integrals</title>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Solar photovoltaic (PV) cells are one of the world's
        fastest-growing energy source.
        The rate of solar PV production, <m>S</m>,
        in gigawatts per year,
        is approximated by <m>S(t)=0.277e^{0.368t}</m>, where
        <m>t</m> is in years since 2000.
      </p>

      <task workspace="10%">
        <p>
          Write down the definite integral that gives the total solar PV
          production between <m>2000</m> and <m>2010</m>.
        </p>
      </task>

      <task workspace="10%">
        <p>
          Estimate the total solar PV production between <m>2000</m> and <m>2010</m> using
          <m>R_5</m>.
          Is this an overestimate or an underestimate?
        </p>
      </task>

      <task>
        <p>
          Use R to find the exact value of the total change in production predicted by the model <m>S(t)</m>.
        </p>

        <p>
          R command <fillin characters="10"/>
        </p>

        <p>
          Total change in production <fillin characters="10"/>
        </p>
      </task>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        A forest fire covers 2000 acres at time <m>t=0</m>.
        The fire grows at the
        rate of <m>8\sqrt{t}</m> acres per hour,
        where <m>t</m> is in hours.
        (Note: an acre is
        1/640 sq mi and about
        <quantity><mag>0.404</mag><unit base="hectare"/></quantity>.)
      </p>

      <task workspace="10%">
        <p>
          Write down the definite integral that gives the amount by which the area
          of the fire increases between <m>t = 0</m> and <m>t = 30</m>.
        </p>
      </task>

      <task workspace="10%">
        <p>
          Estimate the increase in area between <m>t = 0</m> and <m>t = 30</m>,
          using <m>L_6</m>.
          Is this an overestimate or an underestimate?
        </p>
      </task>

      <task>
        <p>
          Use R to find how many acres are on fire at <m>t = 30</m>.
        </p>

        <p>
          R command <fillin characters="10"/>
        </p>

        <p>
          Total area on fire <fillin characters="10"/>
        </p>
      </task>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

